specs/approved/generic-clean-priority-co.message:
Hey Dmitry, Jay,
Is the below method of overriding the priority and params for clean steps preferred?

clean_step_overrides=deploy.erase_devices:{'priority':10,'params':..},management.reset_bios_to_default:{'priority':10,'params':...}

oslo.config has MultiOpt type that allows several instances of the same option to be merged in a list. I suggest we use it here to avoid unreadable long lines, e.g.:

 clean_step_add_params=step1:{k:v,k2:v2}
 clean_step_add_params=step2:{k:v,k3:v3}

we might want to allow it for priority_overrides too, but this is optional

specs/approved/evolve-error-responses.rs.message:
It's not only that. Currently what we return is different even for different errors. E.g. for 401 we return:

 {"error": {"message": "The request you have made requires authentication.", "code": 401, "title": "Unauthorized"}}

which is close. But e.g. for node not found we return:

 {"error_message": "{\"debuginfo\": null, \"faultcode\": \"Client\", \"faultstring\": \"Node foo could not be found.\"}"}

which is something completely different. Do you suggest changing that? I'm all for it, but we need to understand that it's a complete change of the format.

